<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Yes, Nice comment, I agree with you. PVP server gives risk and thats what makes it great.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tarquin">Tarquin</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:24 p.m. 15/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Yes, Nice comment, I agree with you. PVP server gives risk and thats what makes it great.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1427" TARGET=_self>Re: My hopes...</A> (st)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> What I will be watching is the creativness and swiftness to

<BR>&gt; which the GM's can keep an evenness. Beyond all else I have seen
<BR>&gt; the designs strive for a near perfect sense of balance. It is
<BR>&gt; true that no single race or class has any distict advantage. The
<BR>&gt; same holds true for the areas of the lands.
<P>&gt; My hope is that the GM's have enough power to go beyond the game
<BR>&gt; set. To be able to alter things as we begin to live in
<BR>&gt; "sony's world".
<P>I just wouldn't want GM's forcing people to behave in some special roleplay manner.
<P>&gt; My biggest fear is that we will eveolve into a horde of name
<BR>&gt; callers. that we might end up doing nothing but wanting to do
<BR>&gt; nothing but bake those striving to get a toehold, with the toys
<BR>&gt; of the game (spells and weapons)... how terribly small and
<BR>&gt; boring.
<P>&gt; The creative implementation in play possibilities of the PvP+
<BR>&gt; server are unmatched on any other server. I have found a bonding
<BR>&gt; the goes well beyond anything else. We know we are ALWAYS at
<BR>&gt; risk.. so we watch each other. Here alone, zone boundries are
<BR>&gt; NOT a road to safety but rather a potential lethal trap! That
<BR>&gt; rush.. is spin rakeing.
<P>Hell yea :) hehe bandits all over telling you to drop your gold (hehe I recall doing this :P)..hehe It is much more fun
<P>on normal servers people will get bored... and look if i wanna fight you and you refuse, and im tipsy or just pissed, I can do NOTHING if u dont accept my duel..so what will happen? person will start calling you names and tyring to tip you off into accepting duel.. now this doesn't happen on PVP server because u dont need other person's confirmation..
<BR>so you chose
<P>NAME CALLING vs NO TALK PVP.. (which is much less of a "rpg" threat as silence is a characteristic of a killer)..
<P>-Tarquin ,playerkiller... or I should be "more correct"... playerfighter...
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
